ossess mourning, he argues that for several of them reclaimed mourning opened a door onto a strange and fresh understanding of experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362641640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626416423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626416/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles